rules:
  # Component Development
  - Create reusable components in `/src/components/common/`
  - Create page-specific components in `/src/components/pages/`
  - Use props for component communication
  - Use events for child-to-parent communication
  - Use the event bus (`$bus`) for global communication

  # Component Structure
  - Use single-file components (.vue) with template, script, and style sections
  - Follow Vue 2 Options API patterns
  - Use proper component lifecycle management
  - Implement proper component state management

  # Props and Events
  - Use props for parent-to-child communication
  - Use events for child-to-parent communication
  - Use the event bus for global communication
  - Follow the established event naming conventions

  # Styling and Theming
  - Use SCSS for styling with proper nesting
  - Follow the established theme patterns
  - Use CoreUI components for consistent UI
  - Use Bootstrap Vue components for form elements
  - Implement responsive design patterns

  # Component Patterns
  - Use the established component patterns
  - Follow the established component lifecycle patterns
  - Use the established component state patterns
  - Implement proper component error handling

  # Performance
  - Use proper component lifecycle management
  - Implement proper component state management
  - Use computed properties for expensive operations
  - Follow the established performance patterns

  # Accessibility
  - Use proper ARIA attributes
  - Implement proper keyboard navigation
  - Use proper semantic HTML
  - Follow the established accessibility patterns

